$ sp_execute_external_script

Run a script in the *extensibility framework*.

The script must be written in (as of SQL Server 2017) → development/languages/R[R] or → development/languages/Python[Python]. SQL Server Preview 2019 additionally seems\
to support also → development/languages/Java[Java].

If using R, generally, the output of `sp_execute_external_script` is limited to a single → development/languages/R/data-structures/data-frame[data frame].
-
Howerver, additional scalars can be returned using the `@params` paremeter.

sa:
  R package → development/languages/R/packages/sqlmlutils[sqlmlutils]
